(54, 1, '2011-04-02 04:08:15', '2011-04-02 04:08:15', 'The young Austrian violinist Martha Khadem-Missagh, born in November 1979, started playing the violin at the age of three, gave her first public performance with five and debut as soloist with orchestra at the age of nine.\r\n \r\n    She continues the musical tradition in the fourth generation. She received first violin lessons from her father and Margarete Biedermann. She studied with Eugenia Polatschek at the Conservatory of Music Vienna, and at the Academy of Music and Performing Arts Vienna with Gerhard Schulz (Alban Berg Quartet) and Christian Altenburger. Masterclasses with Robert McDuffie, Rainer Kussmaul, Krzysztof Wegrzyn.\r\n \r\n   Concerts throughout Europe, USA, South \r\n\r\n<a href=" http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/video.mp4">video</a>\r\n<a href=" http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/article_bg1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-58" title="article_bg" src=" http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/article_bg1.png" alt="" width="791" height="554" /></a>', 'Martha Khadem-Missagh', 'Austria', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'martha-khadem-missagh', '', '', '2011-04-02 18:24:03', '2011-04-02 18:24:03', '', 0, 'http://www.musicandmore.lu/wp/?p=54', 0, 'post', '', 0),
